-- Russia Equity Movers: Mail.ru, Rosneft, Lukoil, Black Earth
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-02-24T17:00:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/russia-equity-movers-mail-ru-rosneft-lukoil-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock Micex index rose 3.7
percent to 1,594.55 by the close in Moscow, its biggest advance
in three months. The dollar-denominated RTS index gained 5
percent to 1,722.05.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Black Earth Farming Ltd. (BEFSDB)   dropped to the lowest
price in almost two months, sliding 3.5 percent to 14 kronor.
The Stockholm-listed Russian grain producer reported its net
loss widened last year because of bad crop quality.  Mail.ru Group Ltd. (MAIL)   climbed 8.2 percent to $38.20,
the highest intraday price since July 27. The largest Russian-
language Internet companyâ€™s London-traded global depositary
receipts advanced after it reported net income in the second
half of 2011 almost tripled from a year earlier to $122.9
million.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN)  (ROSN RX) gained 3.9 percent to 225.55 rubles
and  OAO Lukoil (LKOH)  (LKOH RX) added 5.2 percent to 1,871.20 rubles,
its biggest gain based on closing prices since October 2009. Oil
increased as much as 1.1 percent to $108.99 a barrel in  New
York , advancing for a seventh day and headed for its longest
winning streak since January 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
